# Testing

Prefer **Vitest** (unit/integration) + **Playwright** (e2e). CI should run lint + typecheck + unit. Repo may still be thin on specs — **when you touch a risk area below, add coverage in the same change**.

## Must cover when touched

| Risk | Minimum assertion |
|---|---|
| Payment webhook | Same `(provider, eventId)` twice → `duplicate: true`, single capture / single stock commit |
| Inventory | `reserve` then `release`/`commit` leaves `onHand`/`reserved` consistent; `INSUFFICIENT_STOCK` when empty |
| Order / article / campaign transitions | Illegal jump rejected (409 / domain code) |
| AuthZ | Wrong role / other user’s order → 401/403/404, not data leak |
| Medical publish gate | Cannot publish medical-required without approval |
| Writer / campaign payout | Gate + idempotent release |

## How to write them

```typescript
// ✅ test the invariant (fulfillment / inventory service)
await fulfillment.processWebhook({ provider: 'mock', eventId: 'evt_1', … });
await fulfillment.processWebhook({ provider: 'mock', eventId: 'evt_1', … }); // duplicate

// ❌ only snapshot JSX class names
```

- Fake clocks/network — no `sleep(1000)` flakes.
- New production bug → regression test when feasible.
- E2E smoke for critical journeys: checkout, article publish, reverse-bid award — not for every formatter.
- Never disable failing critical tests to greenwash CI.
